name: The Pattern of Zebra
description: I always enjoy the process of learning to take pictures, especially when learning about basic photography techniques. For me it is very important to be mastered so that it runs reflexively. Until now I always do that, back to basics in an effort to continue to practice shooting skills. Besides being an important part of a work journey, it is also very influential in making future works. This photo is part of a photographic composition exercise, made to meet the final exam for the photography composition course during college. Taken at the Gembira Loka zoo, Yogyakarta, Indonesia.
